item.title: I cant regster on mopar status page
item.dc:creator: @King_Redrum King Redrum
item.description:
@King_Redrum wrote:

Scroll to the bottom of the server status page until you see some text that looks like this; “Click here to register your own server.”. In short, you can just go here to begin registering your server: http://www.moparisthebest.com/serverstatus.php?action=register.

Once you click that, type in the name of your server, such as “Frozen PKz”.
Then put in the IP address which you say is frozenpkz.no-ip.biz.
The port is already set to 43594, if you’re using a port besides 43593 such as 5555, then change it to your port number, otherwise leave it.
Then put in the password you want so that you can change it later if needed, then re-type your password again in the box below it.

Then there’s info, pretty self explained by the word “Info”. Just enter some information about your server.

E.G.

"This is testscape source with slight editing.

Easy/Hard/Medium training.

Plenty of commands." and etc.

Hopefully this helps.
